1
00:00:00,010 --> 00:00:19,930
Watch on kissasia.li

2
00:00:13,323 --> 00:00:15,628
(Kim Myung Soo)

3
00:00:19,815 --> 00:00:22,057
(Kang Min Ah)

4
00:00:42,665 --> 00:00:45,181
(Love In Sync)

5
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,229
(All people, incidents, and backgrounds...)

6
00:00:48,230 --> 00:00:49,230
(in this drama are fictitious and unrelated to reality.)

7
00:00:49,231 --> 00:00:50,300
(Also, children and animals were filmed under production guidelines.)

8
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,600
(Ward A)

9
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:55,340
Hey, our Yu Star. Yu Star.

10
00:00:55,970 --> 00:00:56,970
Ji An, are you okay?

11
00:00:57,410 --> 00:01:00,780
You're not hurt, are you? You're completely fine, right?

12
00:01:01,340 --> 00:01:03,510
At least, I was until you got here.

13
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:06,580
Can't you see?

14
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:09,850
I told you not to call him.

15
00:01:11,250 --> 00:01:12,589
- Hey, Manager Kim. - Yes.

16
00:01:12,590 --> 00:01:14,020
Contact the legal team right away...

17
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:15,389
and tell them to sue Millennium Bodhisattva...

18
00:01:15,390 --> 00:01:17,260
or Mental Care punk, or whatever his name is.

19
00:01:17,330 --> 00:01:19,760
- Understood. - No, a lawsuit is a bit much.

20
00:01:20,260 --> 00:01:22,400
I'm really fine. I'm perfectly all right.

21
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,430
It was an accident. Don't overreact.

22
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:26,439
How do you know if it was an accident or on purpose?

23
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:28,740
You were right. You should not trust people.

24
00:01:28,970 --> 00:01:30,840
Before he goes and spreads nasty rumours about you,

25
00:01:30,910 --> 00:01:33,280
- we need to strike first. - He's not like that.

26
00:01:36,410 --> 00:01:37,410
Why?

27
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:39,880
What?

28
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:44,790
Was that a line from a script, "He's not like that?"

29
00:01:45,620 --> 00:01:48,160
I know, right? Coming from you, who distrusts everyone,

30
00:01:48,220 --> 00:01:49,560
that's not a line I ever expected to hear.

31
00:01:50,330 --> 00:01:52,160
No. Well... I mean...

32
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,260
I just don't want things to get complicated.

33
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:56,900
Can't you see?

34
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:09,410
(VIP Room)

35
00:02:09,510 --> 00:02:13,050
What did I tell you? I said that therapist can draw out emotions...

36
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:15,890
that a person has suppressed without even realising it.

37
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:18,120
I can't believe that brat had such humanity...

38
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:20,620
suppressed in her subconscious. That Bodhisattva is the real deal.

39
00:02:27,930 --> 00:02:29,130
I wonder if she's okay.

40
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:37,610
(For Mind And Body)

41
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:41,510
I wonder if she's okay.

42
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:47,080
What was that just now?

43
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:50,850
Hey.

44
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:52,590
Hey.

45
00:02:54,290 --> 00:02:55,890
Did you just ask me if I was okay?

46
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:58,760
I was the one sleeping,

47
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:01,000
so why are you the one talking in your sleep?

48
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:03,230
You didn't ask if I was okay?

49
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:06,700
I can see you're fine with my own two eyes, so why would I ask?

50
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:09,410
It's not like we're that close anyway.

51
00:03:10,470 --> 00:03:12,980
Why are you here? Go sleep at your own place.

52
00:03:13,210 --> 00:03:14,910
I'd love to.

53
00:03:15,450 --> 00:03:17,780
But you know, it's raining outside...

54
00:03:20,650 --> 00:03:21,650
Has it stopped?

55
00:03:25,090 --> 00:03:27,790
If you want me to leave, I'll gladly do as you wish.

56
00:03:29,790 --> 00:03:30,790
Stay.

57
00:03:35,730 --> 00:03:39,170
You're not a child. Why can't you be alone just because it's raining?

58
00:03:43,940 --> 00:03:45,940
A fear that responds to a specific condition...

59
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:49,110
is a conditioned trigger response. A form of trauma.

60
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:50,710
In your childhood,

61
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:54,120
did you ever experience a major accident?

62
00:03:55,790 --> 00:03:58,250
He's good, I'll give him that.

63
00:03:59,260 --> 00:04:01,020
(Dong Gyeong Kitchen)

64
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,560
Oh, it hurts.

65
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,400
Oh, it hurts.

66
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,900
Be gentle.

67
00:04:12,470 --> 00:04:13,970
Stop being a baby.

68
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,640
I said it hurts.

69
00:04:16,770 --> 00:04:19,640
Of course it hurts, you punk. Your back is a complete mess.

70
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:23,550
What in the world happened to you?

71
00:04:24,050 --> 00:04:26,320
Hey, say something. Stop driving me crazy.

72
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,220
It was just something.

73
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:31,190
- So what is this "something?" - I said, it was just something.

74
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,689
- Did you get in a fight? - No.

75
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:34,520
- Oh, you got beaten up. - No, I didn't.

76
00:04:34,590 --> 00:04:36,260
- You so got beaten up. - I said no.

77
00:04:36,330 --> 00:04:37,589
How many hits did you take and how much money did they get?

78
00:04:37,590 --> 00:04:40,660
- Is it a penny a punch? - I told you, no.

79
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:45,600
As a member of her fan club, all you have to do is be grateful to me.

80
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:49,970
- Did you get hit in the head? - Seriously.

81
00:04:59,380 --> 00:05:02,490
Gosh. This punk. Oh, right.

82
00:05:04,820 --> 00:05:06,319
Has this guy been a sucker his whole life?

83
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:09,060
Seriously, what is this? Darn it.

84
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:12,860
Hey, here... Can't you see this spilled coffee?

85
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,300
What are you even wiping? You're not going to clean this up?

86
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,300
I'm sorry.

87
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,540
Hey, I'm telling you, okay?

88
00:05:20,970 --> 00:05:24,510
That idiot wired 50,000 dollars straight to my bank account.

89
00:05:24,870 --> 00:05:27,910
How can there be so many dumbasses in the world?

90
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:31,910
Gosh. What are you talking about? It's not fraud.

91
00:05:32,050 --> 00:05:34,050
- Unbelievable. - Please, please, just a minute.

92
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,819
- I'm so sick of this. - Wait.

93
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:39,960
Please, please give me my money back. I'm begging you, please.

94
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:41,820
Seriously, darn it.

95
00:05:42,730 --> 00:05:45,230
This is driving me crazy.

96
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:49,400
I told you not to come. I told you not to come.

97
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:51,170
Did I tell you or not? Huh?

98
00:05:51,970 --> 00:05:54,099
Why do you keep coming here and bothering me?

99
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:56,570
It's gone. It's gone. I told you, it's gone, you moron.

100
00:05:57,070 --> 00:05:59,840
Is this woman insane? Darn it.

101
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:02,510
Gosh, this punk... I said I didn't do wrong.

102
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:04,150
I didn't do anything wrong.

103
00:06:04,650 --> 00:06:06,750
Okay, I get it. Gosh.

104
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:09,790
I had to beg Director Kang to get this meeting, so...

105
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:11,120
don't say anything snarky.

106
00:06:11,290 --> 00:06:13,790
- I get it. - And don't lose your temper.

107
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:18,760
- I said I get it. - Be sweet when you answer...

108
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,200
and be as sincere as you can.

109
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,770
I said I get it.

110
00:06:23,870 --> 00:06:26,200
Hey, when's your next therapy session scheduled?

111
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,700
You have so much love for humanity in that subconscious of yours.

112
00:06:29,910 --> 00:06:31,610
Do we really have to have this meeting?

113
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,040
Gosh, this girl...

114
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:34,840
You're not grasping the situation.

115
00:06:34,910 --> 00:06:36,110
Do you not know who Director Moon is?

116
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:39,080
Of course, I know who he is. He's a master of Korean cinema.

117
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,150
Every movie he makes is a guaranteed blockbuster.

118
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,850
Every actor who works with him...

119
00:06:42,990 --> 00:06:44,590
ends up winning awards at festivals at home and abroad.

120
00:06:44,650 --> 00:06:45,860
He's a deity when it comes to directing actors.

121
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,420
You talked my ear off about it on the way here.

122
00:06:48,930 --> 00:06:49,930
So you do know.

123
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:53,530
But sucking up to people and acting all cute isn't my style.

124
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:57,500
Hey, it's not like I enjoy catering to your every whim either.

125
00:06:58,770 --> 00:07:02,610
Listen carefully. This is a critical time for you.

126
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:06,840
You're almost 30. Your days of getting by on looks are numbered.

127
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:09,149
Every day, younger and prettier girls...

128
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:10,150
are going to be coming up behind you.

129
00:07:10,350 --> 00:07:13,080
Do you really think you can survive in this industry?

130
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,119
If you don't transition from being the star Yu Ji An...

131
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:18,120
to the actress Yu Ji An right now,

132
00:07:18,690 --> 00:07:21,920
your career as a celebrity won't last much longer.

133
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:23,860
Remember that.

134
00:07:25,060 --> 00:07:28,460
- I hope you remember too, sir. - What's that?

135
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,870
That I haven't signed my contract renewal yet.

136
00:07:38,010 --> 00:07:39,010
Hello.

137
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:42,210
Sorry.

138
00:07:42,950 --> 00:07:44,150
Well, this is an interesting situation.

139
00:07:44,810 --> 00:07:46,920
I didn't know Director Moon had invited Han Yi Jin...

140
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:49,750
and I invited you two without him knowing.

141
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:53,460
Right, well.

142
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:57,290
Please, sit. Ji An, have a seat.

143
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:05,430
I read the screenplay you sent over,

144
00:08:05,740 --> 00:08:08,640
and it looks like you have another masterpiece on your hands.

145
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,040
Is that so?

146
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:12,380
Now we just need to get the casting right.

147
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:19,550
Our Ji An here is a huge fan of your work, Director.

148
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:21,350
Yes.

149
00:08:21,820 --> 00:08:23,590
Really? That's surprising.

150
00:08:24,220 --> 00:08:25,490
Which of my films in particular?

151
00:08:26,220 --> 00:08:28,860
Well...

152
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:31,290
"The Solitary Island?"

153
00:08:32,860 --> 00:08:33,860
What did you like about it?

154
00:08:34,830 --> 00:08:35,830
How should I put it?

155
00:08:36,370 --> 00:08:38,300
I guess it was the desperation of someone...

156
00:08:38,370 --> 00:08:40,000
trying to survive against all odds.

157
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:43,970
No. It was not about desperation.

158
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:48,280
It's a desire.

159
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:50,909
The ugly desire of a human who'd trample...

160
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:53,650
over everyone else just to survive.

161
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:59,120
For people like you, Yu Ji An,

162
00:08:59,490 --> 00:09:00,990
it might be difficult to interpret.

163
00:09:08,860 --> 00:09:12,270
Art is open to interpretation, after all. Yes.

164
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,100
Let's not waste any more of our precious time.

165
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,710
Let's get straight to the point.

166
00:09:19,140 --> 00:09:21,510
I have no intention of casting Yu Ji An...

167
00:09:22,340 --> 00:09:23,350
in my movie whatsoever.

168
00:09:25,410 --> 00:09:27,150
Director Moon.

169
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:30,590
Director, let's not be so definitive.

170
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:34,190
Your acting style, Yu Ji An, is exactly what I despise.

171
00:09:35,420 --> 00:09:37,760
A kid who's never truly experienced life...

172
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:41,160
cries and laughs with acting skills bought with money...

173
00:09:41,830 --> 00:09:43,530
There is no sincerity at your acting.

174
00:09:57,210 --> 00:09:58,210
Director.

175
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:00,650
Do you have a crush on me?

176
00:10:01,850 --> 00:10:03,420
Ji An, are you crazy?

177
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:07,120
No, it's just he seems to know so much about me.

178
00:10:07,890 --> 00:10:09,160
If that isn't love, what is?

179
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:11,760
Even haters need to have some affection to do what they do.

180
00:10:12,530 --> 00:10:15,360
As someone who used to have a million haters, I would know.

181
00:10:15,830 --> 00:10:17,570
Ji An, that's enough.

182
00:10:19,070 --> 00:10:20,600
You're right about everything, Director.

183
00:10:20,940 --> 00:10:22,970
As a star, I have fame and money,

184
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:26,140
so now I'm getting greedy for the title of "serious actress."

185
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,880
But you don't have to worry.

186
00:10:29,610 --> 00:10:32,010
Because I have no intention of being cast in your movie...

187
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:33,780
either.

188
00:10:34,780 --> 00:10:35,780
And why is that?

189
00:10:36,390 --> 00:10:38,189
Why would I trust a pretentious director...

190
00:10:38,190 --> 00:10:40,520
who doesn't even know what his own movie is about?

191
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:42,760
That movie, "The Solitary Island..."

192
00:10:44,090 --> 00:10:45,260
It is about desperation.

193
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:50,030
How is becoming vile just to survive an "ugly desire?"

194
00:10:50,830 --> 00:10:52,400
It's a darn miserable desperation.

195
00:10:56,470 --> 00:10:58,009
But for a director who was born rich...

196
00:10:58,010 --> 00:10:59,940
and has lived as a rich man his whole life,

197
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:03,180
I guess that desperation could seem ugly.

198
00:11:04,610 --> 00:11:06,820
They call you the Crown Prince of the film industry, right?

199
00:11:07,450 --> 00:11:08,620
Since you're so bourgeois.

200
00:11:10,650 --> 00:11:12,960
What would someone like that know about desperation?

201
00:11:13,990 --> 00:11:15,020
What a jerk.

202
00:11:16,890 --> 00:11:19,700
Hey, Ji An. What is wrong with you?

203
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:23,600
Well, it seems like we've both laid all our cards on the table.

204
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,500
I'll be taking my leave now.

205
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:29,940
Hey, hey, Ji An.

206
00:11:31,310 --> 00:11:32,310
Hey, Yu Ji An.

207
00:11:32,910 --> 00:11:33,910
Hey.

208
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:41,750
She's quite interesting.

209
00:11:43,490 --> 00:11:45,120
Right, Director Moon?

210
00:11:50,490 --> 00:11:51,490
Hey, Yu Star.

211
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:53,930
Hey, you, I...

212
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:57,130
Hurry up and go inside to apologise to Director Moon.

213
00:11:57,530 --> 00:11:59,130
No. Why should I?

214
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:03,210
Don't you know he's famous in this business for being rude and a jerk?

215
00:12:03,310 --> 00:12:07,340
- I know. - Then why did you lose your temper?

216
00:12:07,510 --> 00:12:10,250
But I also have a reputation in this business for being a brat.

217
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:11,680
So, there.

218
00:12:18,290 --> 00:12:20,220
Darn it, she almost convinced me.

219
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:24,430
(Moon Pictures)

220
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,270
Hello, Ji An's Mother.

221
00:12:35,570 --> 00:12:37,310
I'm doing fine.

222
00:12:38,070 --> 00:12:39,680
Is everything okay in the US?

223
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:44,409
Gosh.

224
00:12:44,410 --> 00:12:47,720
You never seem to forget when it's time to renew Ji An's contract.

225
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:49,920
Yes.

226
00:12:50,850 --> 00:12:51,850
Excuse me?

227
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:56,090
(Cha Eun Hwan)

228
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:58,760
Sir, we have a huge problem.

229
00:12:59,130 --> 00:13:01,360
- What is it? What's wrong? - It's Lee Young Ji.

230
00:13:01,430 --> 00:13:02,430
What about Young Ji?

231
00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:09,940
The recent stabbing rampage in Dongjin District, Seoul...

232
00:13:10,010 --> 00:13:12,369
was believed to be an act of revenge by a past fraud victim...

233
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:14,510
against her perpetrator.

234
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:17,480
But an investigation has revealed that a counsellor...

235
00:13:17,550 --> 00:13:19,450
who had been offering her free sessions...

236
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:22,990
had actually encouraged this act of revenge,

237
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,590
sparking a major controversy.

238
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,960
Hello, this is Cha Eun Hwan.

239
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:39,600
What? Questioning as a witness?

240
00:13:56,850 --> 00:14:00,520
Listen carefully. This is a critical time for you.

241
00:14:01,660 --> 00:14:02,660
You're almost 30.

242
00:14:02,730 --> 00:14:05,090
Your days of getting by on looks are numbered.

243
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:07,530
Every day, younger and prettier girls...

244
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:09,700
are going to be coming up behind you.

245
00:14:10,370 --> 00:14:12,000
Do you really think you can survive in this industry?

246
00:14:15,740 --> 00:14:17,270
I should've just put up with it.

247
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:35,860
Hello?

248
00:14:38,260 --> 00:14:39,630
Well...

249
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,500
I'm just...

250
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:45,600
Really?

251
00:14:46,140 --> 00:14:47,940
For real? Are you serious?

252
00:14:49,940 --> 00:14:51,610
("Yu Ji An: Star To Actress, Director Moon's Cinderella")

253
00:14:52,570 --> 00:14:53,840
Yi Jin, I'm sorry.

254
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:58,350
I can teach acting, but I can't teach charm. That's just how it is.

255
00:14:58,910 --> 00:15:00,250
I'm sorry. I hope you understand.

256
00:15:12,060 --> 00:15:14,530
Yi Jin.

257
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:17,970
I heard back from Erbeni.

258
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:22,570
- They can't sponsor you right now. - Mi Jeong.

259
00:15:25,070 --> 00:15:27,410
Are you still struggling to pay your mom's hospital bills?

260
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:30,450
What? Why do you ask?

261
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,820
("Last Day On Earth," "Dream In The Fridge")

262
00:15:41,490 --> 00:15:43,230
I haven't seen that look on your face in a while.

263
00:15:43,990 --> 00:15:46,559
When you got your first lead role after becoming an actress?

264
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:50,400
I don't think I've seen it since. Are you that excited?

265
00:15:51,530 --> 00:15:53,170
No, not really.

266
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,670
It's written all over your face.

267
00:15:58,270 --> 00:16:01,080
Ji An, about our contract renewal...

268
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:04,050
Let's talk about that later.

269
00:16:04,550 --> 00:16:05,750
What's the rush?

270
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:09,150
Right. No rush at all.

271
00:16:17,630 --> 00:16:19,460
Sorry, everyone. I got stuck in traffic.

272
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:28,370
So, shall we finalise the details and sign the contracts?

273
00:16:46,420 --> 00:16:50,790
(Exposing Actress Y, A Former Girl Group Member)

274
00:16:57,870 --> 00:16:59,770
(I styled the person in this video for three years.)

275
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,800
(I agonized over writing this, but I can no longer stay silent.)

276
00:17:06,010 --> 00:17:07,710
(Post)

277
00:17:13,580 --> 00:17:16,390
So? You're quitting now, of all times?

278
00:17:16,850 --> 00:17:20,190
Yes, my mom... She's sick.

279
00:17:20,390 --> 00:17:23,730
I have to take care of her.

280
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:27,760
How can you be so irresponsible?

281
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:30,500
We're just about to start shooting. If we change stylists now,

282
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:33,170
who's going to be responsible for the character's wardrobe continuity?

283
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:35,700
I'm so sorry.

284
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:40,340
Is your bank account number still the same?

285
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:43,950
- What? - Don't worry about hospital bills.

286
00:17:44,580 --> 00:17:45,780
I'll take care of it.

287
00:17:47,450 --> 00:17:48,450
Ji An...

288
00:17:50,390 --> 00:17:52,150
Just go and do your job.

289
00:17:54,060 --> 00:17:55,060
Okay.

290
00:18:15,210 --> 00:18:16,880
(Post Published Successfully. OK)

291
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:18,710
(That's not a new attitude. It's her personality.)

292
00:18:18,780 --> 00:18:20,220
(Every word from her mouth is meant to put someone down.)

293
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,880
Do you have any idea...

294
00:18:21,950 --> 00:18:22,950
- what's happening now? - What is this?

295
00:18:23,190 --> 00:18:25,250
- Isn't that Yu Ji An? - Hey, come look at this.

296
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,620
- That's totally Yu Ji An. - What is it?

297
00:18:26,790 --> 00:18:29,260
- Is that Yu Ji An? - The one in red.

298
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:32,090
Gosh. You can't treat your own staff like that.

299
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:34,300
- There's something wrong with her. - No way, is this AI-generated?

300
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:36,400
("Yu Ji An: Verbal Abuse Video Goes Viral, Igniting Controversy")

301
00:18:36,570 --> 00:18:37,970
I always had a weird feeling about her, though.

302
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:40,800
- Exactly. I knew she was like that. - But something feels weird.

303
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:43,210
Looks like Yu Ji An's image is about to go down the drain.

304
00:18:43,410 --> 00:18:45,670
You can't trust the images celebrities sell.

305
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:46,880
This is insane.

306
00:18:47,010 --> 00:18:48,610
(She has a pretty face, but she has so many anger.)

307
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:49,749
Our Yu Ji An went too far this time.

308
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:52,080
- Is she crazy? - Yu Ji An has a crazy temper.

309
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:53,450
I knew it from the start.

310
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:56,150
My sister knows her and says she's a total psycho.

311
00:18:56,220 --> 00:18:57,920
She shouldn't have abused her power like that.

312
00:18:58,050 --> 00:18:59,420
(Film Contract)

313
00:19:06,630 --> 00:19:10,100
Then let's forget the past and work well together going forward.

314
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:16,410
I look forward to working with you.

315
00:19:18,540 --> 00:19:19,640
Excuse me, Director.

316
00:19:24,950 --> 00:19:28,150
A video of her bullying just blew up online.

317
00:19:29,550 --> 00:19:30,550
What?

318
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:38,160
Do you have any idea what's happening now?

319
00:19:38,530 --> 00:19:40,700
This is so frustrating. It's driving me crazy.

320
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:43,100
How did it come to this, all because of one person?

321
00:19:43,430 --> 00:19:46,100
Why are you crying again? Why are you crying?

322
00:19:46,230 --> 00:19:48,540
I'm the one who should be crying because of you.

323
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:51,910
Is that really you?

324
00:19:52,810 --> 00:19:53,810
Did you do that?

325
00:19:54,340 --> 00:19:56,780
No way I...

326
00:19:57,810 --> 00:19:58,810
It wasn't me.

327
00:19:59,310 --> 00:20:00,380
There's no way I...

328
00:20:00,580 --> 00:20:02,750
So are you saying the video was doctored?

329
00:20:03,190 --> 00:20:04,450
That Mi Jeong lied?

330
00:20:05,950 --> 00:20:09,320
Mi Jeong. You have her number, right? Let me see her.

331
00:20:10,090 --> 00:20:11,330
She's unreachable.

332
00:20:11,730 --> 00:20:16,130
Even if you could, contacting her now would be seen as a threat.

333
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:18,530
You'll just make things worse.

334
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,770
Then what am I supposed to do?

335
00:20:22,540 --> 00:20:25,939
(J.An Entertainment)

336
00:20:25,940 --> 00:20:27,340
It wasn't me.

337
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:30,480
No matter how rude or obnoxious I am...

338
00:20:31,010 --> 00:20:35,780
I wouldn't go this far... Right, I wouldn't do this. Right?

339
00:20:48,430 --> 00:20:51,300
Ji An, calm down and think.

340
00:20:51,730 --> 00:20:53,740
There must be some context to this, right?

341
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:57,210
We need to know what happened so we can make a statement or an excuse.

342
00:20:59,670 --> 00:21:01,080
Hey. Snap out of it.

343
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,980
If you can't fix this, your career is over. Got it?

344
00:21:08,420 --> 00:21:11,390
I think she's already on board. The express train to rock bottom.

345
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:15,060
Advertisers are already talking about breach of contract fees.

346
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:17,560
This is going to be a big hit.

347
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:34,710
Director Kim. Getting dropped?

348
00:21:35,180 --> 00:21:37,650
Does it make sense to drop the lead actress mid-season?

349
00:21:38,180 --> 00:21:40,120
This isn't the 1980s.

350
00:21:40,650 --> 00:21:43,620
Why are you suddenly sending the lead character to study abroad?

351
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:45,820
Look, if you keep writing false articles like this,

352
00:21:45,950 --> 00:21:48,059
we'll have no choice but to take legal action. Seriously.

353
00:21:48,060 --> 00:21:50,330
No, block all social media comments now.

354
00:21:50,390 --> 00:21:52,190
Not just on her accounts,

355
00:21:52,260 --> 00:21:55,460
but for all videos that come up when you search for Yu Ji An.

356
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:57,330
Do it now, as fast as you can.

357
00:22:18,590 --> 00:22:19,590
Gosh.

358
00:22:20,220 --> 00:22:23,430
In a situation like this, you chose sparkling water over soju.

359
00:22:23,590 --> 00:22:25,960
That's Ji An, the queen of self-control.

360
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,930
I lost my honour and my popularity,

361
00:22:30,670 --> 00:22:33,670
but do I have to lose my looks too?

362
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:36,000
I have to protect what I can.

363
00:22:36,270 --> 00:22:40,340
You're joking, so I guess you're doing okay?

364
00:22:41,910 --> 00:22:45,710
Do I look okay? Think before you speak.

365
00:22:46,410 --> 00:22:48,850
Hey. Go home.

366
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:51,150
I don't want to be embarrassed anymore.

367
00:22:54,060 --> 00:22:56,420
(Gangseong Police Station)

368
00:22:57,060 --> 00:22:58,530
Don't worry too much.

369
00:22:58,930 --> 00:23:00,630
It's just questioning for a witness statement.

370
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,600
You won't have any major legal liability.

371
00:23:20,250 --> 00:23:22,220
(Ministry of Law)

372
00:23:22,820 --> 00:23:25,490
Ms. Lee Young Ji has refused to see you.

373
00:23:48,980 --> 00:23:55,720
(For The New Members...)

374
00:24:17,270 --> 00:24:18,340
That bastard.

375
00:24:19,540 --> 00:24:20,710
This is all my fault.

376
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:23,080
Because of a scumbag like me.

377
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:30,790
What? Am I hearing things again?

378
00:24:31,650 --> 00:24:33,190
What is wrong with me?

379
00:24:35,060 --> 00:24:37,430
Stress.

380
00:24:38,660 --> 00:24:41,660
No wonder I'm hearing things.

381
00:24:45,300 --> 00:24:47,500
A lowlife like me, giving people counselling.

382
00:24:48,340 --> 00:24:49,600
Healing people?

383
00:24:50,270 --> 00:24:51,270
Comforting them?

384
00:24:52,410 --> 00:24:53,410
You crazy bastard.

385
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:55,640
Wait, but this is too clear to just be in my head.

386
00:24:56,340 --> 00:24:57,510
Why am I being so creepy? This is scary.

387
00:24:58,850 --> 00:25:00,980
Am I possessed or something?

388
00:25:05,390 --> 00:25:06,390
What's with that guy?

389
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:19,600
It's my fault.

390
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:22,440
Because I made the wrong choice...

391
00:25:24,140 --> 00:25:25,270
That poor woman.

392
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:30,450
What the? No way. Am I hearing his thoughts?

393
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:34,880
Gosh. This is impossible.

394
00:25:57,470 --> 00:26:00,110
Are you Yu Ji...

395
00:26:02,110 --> 00:26:03,180
Are you crying right now?

396
00:26:03,710 --> 00:26:04,710
No.

397
00:26:05,380 --> 00:26:06,380
But you are crying.

398
00:26:08,450 --> 00:26:09,580
I said I'm not.

399
00:26:10,220 --> 00:26:12,290
Come on, you're totally crying.

400
00:26:15,020 --> 00:26:16,020
It's just...

401
00:26:17,890 --> 00:26:19,060
Well...

402
00:26:20,900 --> 00:26:22,460
It's not that I'm crying.

403
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,670
I think you're the one who's crying.

404
00:26:26,940 --> 00:26:28,070
What are you talking about?

405
00:26:29,540 --> 00:26:30,970
This feeling of wanting to cry...

406
00:26:32,610 --> 00:26:34,940
I don't think it's my feeling. I think it's yours.

407
00:26:48,790 --> 00:26:49,790
Darn it.

408
00:26:50,290 --> 00:26:52,060
Have I finally lost it? Am I going crazy?

409
00:26:52,430 --> 00:26:54,130
Or did I get drunk on sparkling water?

410
00:26:54,360 --> 00:26:55,929
Darn. I'm the one who's crying,

411
00:26:55,930 --> 00:26:57,530
but I go and say some crap like that to him.

412
00:26:58,030 --> 00:27:00,600
Gosh, I'm nuts. So embarrassing.

413
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:12,480
But it really didn't feel like it was me.

414
00:27:13,380 --> 00:27:14,880
It's not that I'm crying.

415
00:27:15,420 --> 00:27:16,920
I think you're the one who's crying.

416
00:27:18,020 --> 00:27:19,820
Do people just burst into tears like that?

417
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:24,830
(CEO Kim Jun Sik)

418
00:27:32,870 --> 00:27:33,870
Why?

419
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:42,680
Honey, did you sleep well?

420
00:27:43,180 --> 00:27:45,450
What the hell? Why are you in my house looking like that?

421
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:47,350
Take that apron off, now.

422
00:27:47,850 --> 00:27:48,920
Seeing you first thing makes me sick.

423
00:27:49,620 --> 00:27:51,990
Is that any way to talk to the man who saved your life?

424
00:27:53,660 --> 00:27:56,930
Hey, you punk. Do you have any idea who kept you from dying?

425
00:27:57,530 --> 00:28:00,630
I threw out my back carrying your heavy ass home, you brat.

426
00:28:00,700 --> 00:28:01,700
And you're complaining about my looks?

427
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,160
Sick?

428
00:28:03,730 --> 00:28:04,800
No.

429
00:28:05,500 --> 00:28:07,770
No, I was just thrown by the unfamiliar sight.

430
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:09,200
It was a slip of the tongue.

431
00:28:13,210 --> 00:28:15,740
Oh, Song Hwan, haven't you left for your studio yet?

432
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:17,880
Song Hwan, long time no see.

433
00:28:18,550 --> 00:28:20,380
I told you I don't like you bringing just anyone into the house.

434
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:28,860
Wow, she's as prickly as ever. She hasn't changed a bit.

435
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:30,760
So darn charming.

436
00:28:32,030 --> 00:28:34,060
- I'm sorry. - Sorry my ass.

437
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:35,560
Hey, get something for that hangover.

438
00:28:36,430 --> 00:28:37,430
Alright.

439
00:28:43,710 --> 00:28:46,610
Hey, so... Did you get that thing sorted out?

440
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:50,080
- Not yet. - Darn it.

441
00:28:56,280 --> 00:28:57,750
So that's what you meant.

442
00:28:58,690 --> 00:29:02,390
You know, when you said I should be grateful as the fan club president.

443
00:29:02,460 --> 00:29:03,460
What are you talking about?

444
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,060
And what was with that weird flower pose?

445
00:29:09,300 --> 00:29:10,400
Did you get her autograph?

446
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:13,300
Her number? That might be too much to ask.

447
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:15,340
You followed each other, right?

448
00:29:15,670 --> 00:29:16,870
So, when are you going to introduce me to her?

449
00:29:16,940 --> 00:29:19,670
Oh, and for the record, I want it to look like we met by chance.

450
00:29:20,010 --> 00:29:22,139
Why do you keep using all these abbreviations?

451
00:29:22,140 --> 00:29:24,010
Speak plainly, so I can understand you.

452
00:29:24,210 --> 00:29:27,420
- My love, Yu Ji An. - Right. What about that Yu Ji An?

453
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:29,920
Stop playing around.

454
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:31,790
You don't remember anything?

455
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:37,360
Yu Ji An was the one who saved you. And I was second.

456
00:29:48,670 --> 00:29:53,310
Cha Eun Hwan. Cha Eun Hwan. Are you okay? Hey.

457
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:09,559
- I mean... - Hey, you jerk.

458
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:11,160
Why haven't you been answering? I was worried sick.

459
00:30:12,060 --> 00:30:14,930
- Where are you? - Are you Cha Eun Hwan's friend?

460
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:22,940
Who is this?

461
00:30:23,170 --> 00:30:27,040
Well, something happened to Cha Eun Hwan.

462
00:30:33,450 --> 00:30:35,780
It's really Yu Ji An.

463
00:30:38,250 --> 00:30:40,690
She could have just left after getting in touch with me,

464
00:30:41,220 --> 00:30:44,330
but she stayed by your side because she was worried.

465
00:30:45,630 --> 00:30:48,430
Wow. That's my favourite star.

466
00:30:49,260 --> 00:30:52,370
As the former fan club president, I felt so proud.

467
00:30:54,900 --> 00:30:57,610
But for a star like her, what's with that bullying video?

468
00:30:59,110 --> 00:31:00,240
It must be fake.

469
00:31:02,210 --> 00:31:04,450
It didn't look fake.

470
00:31:05,380 --> 00:31:08,020
Then what? She really did it? Abused her power?

471
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:10,990
My dear Ji An, with that angelic face? What you're saying is...

472
00:31:11,590 --> 00:31:12,590
I'm not so sure.

473
00:31:14,220 --> 00:31:15,420
Even if it wasn't faked,

474
00:31:16,490 --> 00:31:19,590
- something seemed off about it. - Right? What was it?

475
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:27,000
- No, forget it. It's not certain. - Come on.

476
00:31:28,970 --> 00:31:32,570
Why do you always stop halfway? Spit it out. It's so frustrating.

477
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:35,110
It's not frustrating, it's salty. This is really salty.

478
00:31:35,610 --> 00:31:37,480
And you run a restaurant like this?

479
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,610
I have a loyal fanbase, you jerk.

480
00:31:53,390 --> 00:31:54,660
Are you crying right now?

481
00:31:56,130 --> 00:31:57,170
No.

482
00:31:57,470 --> 00:31:58,470
But you are crying.

483
00:32:01,100 --> 00:32:02,240
She must be going through a lot.

484
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:08,410
Well, a 70-30 split isn't bad.

485
00:32:09,580 --> 00:32:11,980
I still have to look at offers from other places,

486
00:32:12,050 --> 00:32:13,480
so don't be too disappointed.

487
00:32:13,780 --> 00:32:15,280
Did you read the contract carefully?

488
00:32:15,620 --> 00:32:17,420
The rest of it is always the same anyway.

489
00:32:18,150 --> 00:32:20,220
I have the right to choose all my projects.

490
00:32:20,620 --> 00:32:22,190
The company pays for all incidental expenses,

491
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:24,290
and I can terminate the contract at any time...

492
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:25,760
without a penalty fee if I want to.

493
00:32:26,630 --> 00:32:28,830
What, are there new clauses?

494
00:32:32,100 --> 00:32:33,170
Listen carefully.

495
00:32:33,700 --> 00:32:34,969
From now on, when you read a contract,

496
00:32:34,970 --> 00:32:37,100
first figure out who has the upper hand...

497
00:32:37,510 --> 00:32:39,740
and who doesn't. Got it?

498
00:32:43,340 --> 00:32:44,810
Well, obviously, I have the upper...

499
00:32:47,780 --> 00:32:48,780
The subordinate party?

500
00:32:48,850 --> 00:32:49,880
(Subordinate Party)

501
00:32:49,950 --> 00:32:50,950
Me?

502
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:54,020
This is ridiculous.

503
00:32:54,360 --> 00:32:55,390
(Profit Split 7:3)

504
00:32:55,460 --> 00:32:56,590
(3X Penalty For Breach Of Contract)

505
00:32:56,990 --> 00:33:00,090
So the 30 percent goes to me, not the company?

506
00:33:04,970 --> 00:33:08,300
You don't seriously think I'm going to sign this darn contract, do you?

507
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:11,610
If you don't want to, you don't have to.

508
00:33:13,740 --> 00:33:15,510
When you were a hot commodity, I bought a building thanks to you,

509
00:33:15,580 --> 00:33:19,650
but when you're not, you're just inventory I have to pay to maintain.

510
00:33:20,450 --> 00:33:24,090
Are you saying you think I'm finished now?

511
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:26,290
Is that why you're treating me like garbage?

512
00:33:27,460 --> 00:33:28,460
Wow.

513
00:33:29,590 --> 00:33:31,330
People can be so cruel.

514
00:33:31,890 --> 00:33:34,600
Just a few days ago, you were grovelling before me.

515
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:39,230
But you know what? I'm not done yet.

516
00:33:39,970 --> 00:33:42,100
A crisis like this? After everything I've been through since my debut?

517
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:44,440
I've dealt with, cleaned up, and endured...

518
00:33:44,510 --> 00:33:46,210
countless crises to get to where I am.

519
00:33:47,340 --> 00:33:48,840
This is no big deal.

520
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:51,580
Just you watch.

521
00:33:52,580 --> 00:33:55,480
I'll reclaim my spot, just to show you.

522
00:34:09,300 --> 00:34:10,300
Just you watch.

523
00:34:11,530 --> 00:34:13,000
You think this is enough to take me down?

524
00:34:21,610 --> 00:34:23,610
(Mom)

525
00:34:28,850 --> 00:34:29,850
Ji An.

526
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,519
Why did you do that?

527
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:33,220
Do you want to go back to the orphanage?

528
00:34:33,350 --> 00:34:34,660
If I quit...

529
00:34:34,720 --> 00:34:36,020
They'd be happy about it.

530
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:40,600
You have to be gone. So the other kids can have a chance.

531
00:34:41,030 --> 00:34:42,600
(Mom)

532
00:34:56,610 --> 00:34:57,650
("Top Star Yu Ji An Is A Free Agent")

533
00:34:57,710 --> 00:34:59,750
What's going on? Why is it so quiet?

534
00:35:01,020 --> 00:35:02,550
Is my phone broken?

535
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:20,170
Hello.

536
00:35:20,600 --> 00:35:21,670
Hello?

537
00:35:22,170 --> 00:35:24,410
This is a call from a public opinion research institute in Seoul...

538
00:35:25,410 --> 00:35:27,710
It's not broken, so why isn't anyone calling?

539
00:35:47,430 --> 00:35:48,530
Yes?

540
00:35:48,860 --> 00:35:50,700
So you're the culprit.

541
00:35:51,100 --> 00:35:52,100
What?

542
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:53,830
What are you talking about all of a sudden?

543
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:59,010
There's no way the industry is this quiet now that I'm a free agent.

544
00:35:59,540 --> 00:36:01,810
All the important calls have always come through you.

545
00:36:02,610 --> 00:36:04,580
So, who has called?

546
00:36:05,250 --> 00:36:06,780
The CEO of Polar Entertainment called, right?

547
00:36:07,580 --> 00:36:10,550
- That guy's been waiting for me... - No one called.

548
00:36:10,650 --> 00:36:12,620
What? No one?

549
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:16,120
You know I'm loyal to you, right? Let me give you a piece of advice.

550
00:36:16,890 --> 00:36:18,730
Before it's too late, go and beg the CEO for forgiveness.

551
00:36:19,790 --> 00:36:20,860
What?

552
00:36:20,930 --> 00:36:22,799
Listen, there isn't a single person in this industry...

553
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:24,100
who would sign you...

554
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:26,000
unless they are completely insane.

555
00:36:26,670 --> 00:36:29,100
Who's going to want an actress whose reputation is in shambles?

556
00:36:29,670 --> 00:36:31,010
The CEO was being generous with that offer...

557
00:36:31,070 --> 00:36:32,309
because of your history together.

558
00:36:32,310 --> 00:36:33,970
- So... - You know what?

559
00:36:35,410 --> 00:36:39,850
Loyal subjects were always the ones who got their heads chopped off.

560
00:36:40,310 --> 00:36:42,480
What? Hello?

561
00:36:54,530 --> 00:36:59,170
I couldn't bear to say this over the phone, so I'm texting you instead.

562
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:02,040
The CEO said you needed to be out of the apartment...

563
00:37:02,670 --> 00:37:03,770
by the end of the week.

564
00:37:04,510 --> 00:37:05,969
I'll always care for you. I'm so sorry.

565
00:37:05,970 --> 00:37:07,240
Your eternal manager, Do Hoon.

566
00:37:18,050 --> 00:37:19,590
What do you think? It's a nice place, right?

567
00:37:20,220 --> 00:37:21,560
It's only on the market as a quick sale...

568
00:37:21,620 --> 00:37:23,590
because the owner got transferred overseas unexpectedly.

569
00:37:23,660 --> 00:37:26,190
It's hard to find a place like this at this price.

570
00:37:26,590 --> 00:37:27,660
Impossible to find.

571
00:37:28,500 --> 00:37:30,660
You said I could move in as early as tomorrow, right?

572
00:37:30,970 --> 00:37:34,770
Of course. So, shall we draw up the contract right now?

573
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:36,040
Sure, why not.

574
00:37:36,340 --> 00:37:37,739
The contract's final...

575
00:37:37,740 --> 00:37:39,670
- once I wire, right? - Exactly.

576
00:37:40,340 --> 00:37:41,380
You've made a good decision.

577
00:37:43,980 --> 00:37:44,980
This way.

578
00:37:45,050 --> 00:37:48,280
(Visiting Room)

579
00:37:48,350 --> 00:37:49,380
Lee Young Ji...

580
00:37:50,180 --> 00:37:51,890
has refused to see you again today.

581
00:38:03,900 --> 00:38:07,300
- We need to get going, don't we? - I keep telling you, you can't.

582
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:11,770
- This is unbelievable. - Why aren't you going in?

583
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:17,280
I'd love to go in. But we can't if she won't let us.

584
00:38:17,610 --> 00:38:18,950
Who are you?

585
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:21,120
What are you doing in someone else's house?

586
00:38:21,650 --> 00:38:23,279
Someone else's house? Please.

587
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:26,290
It's so cliché, everyone says the same thing.

588
00:38:26,420 --> 00:38:27,760
Are you the buyer?

589
00:38:28,160 --> 00:38:29,890
- A buyer? - Or a lease?

590
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:30,960
A lease?

591
00:38:32,390 --> 00:38:33,460
What's that?

592
00:38:34,700 --> 00:38:35,860
You can't be serious.

593
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:38,770
I am asking if you bought this house.

594
00:38:40,030 --> 00:38:41,040
Or did you rent it?

595
00:38:42,740 --> 00:38:44,440
Well, why didn't you just say so?

596
00:38:44,970 --> 00:38:47,170
Hey, what do you take me for?

597
00:38:47,510 --> 00:38:52,010
Look, I don't cheap out and rent things. I buy them outright.

598
00:38:52,510 --> 00:38:53,980
Paid in full. With cash.

599
00:38:54,050 --> 00:38:57,320
Oh, honey. You poor thing. Wow.

600
00:38:57,450 --> 00:38:59,050
What do you mean?

601
00:39:00,090 --> 00:39:01,090
Oh, gosh.

602
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:04,630
What are you people doing in front of my house?

603
00:39:04,930 --> 00:39:07,860
What is this? Two groups in one day? Seriously.

604
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:11,200
Don't tell me you bought the place too?

605
00:39:11,830 --> 00:39:13,199
What are you talking about?

606
00:39:13,200 --> 00:39:15,670
We've paid the final balance and even brought our things.

607
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:19,010
This is so irritating. This isn't the first time.

608
00:39:19,540 --> 00:39:21,210
Just get all this stuff out of here.

609
00:39:24,380 --> 00:39:27,980
(Gangseong Police Station)

610
00:39:28,050 --> 00:39:29,750
(A Police Officer Respected And Loved By The People)

611
00:39:29,820 --> 00:39:32,450
(Gangseong Police Station)

612
00:39:32,890 --> 00:39:35,720
Cha Eun Hwan. It's been ages. Have you been well?

613
00:39:36,060 --> 00:39:37,090
Have you been well?

614
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:39,830
Well, thanks to you, I've quit drinking and doing drugs.

615
00:39:40,290 --> 00:39:41,430
I'm sleeping well too.

616
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:43,900
- I've been doing well. - I'm glad to hear that.

617
00:39:44,200 --> 00:39:47,800
- You keep getting more handsome. - Oh, please.

618
00:39:49,470 --> 00:39:50,800
This is an attempted murder case,

619
00:39:50,870 --> 00:39:52,970
so there isn't much we can do from our end to help.

620
00:39:53,070 --> 00:39:54,440
We don't really have any leverage.

621
00:39:54,910 --> 00:39:57,440
And she already confessed she did it out of revenge.

622
00:39:58,150 --> 00:40:00,610
She'll be lucky if the court shows any leniency.

623
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,580
Have you met with the victim?

624
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:07,990
- No, not yet. - It's not like you're family.

625
00:40:08,890 --> 00:40:11,460
To be honest, the best thing in a situation like this...

626
00:40:11,930 --> 00:40:13,390
is to reach a settlement with the victim.

627
00:40:13,990 --> 00:40:15,899
From the looks of it, Lee Young Ji doesn't have any family...

628
00:40:15,900 --> 00:40:18,130
or friends to help her settle, or anyone at all, for that matter.

629
00:40:19,230 --> 00:40:21,400
Besides, that so-called victim, that con artist bastard...

630
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:23,500
is so slippery.

631
00:40:23,900 --> 00:40:27,010
I mean, all swindlers are, but this guy?

632
00:40:28,010 --> 00:40:29,140
He's the worst of the worst.

633
00:40:29,610 --> 00:40:31,450
During questioning, he didn't show one ounce...

634
00:40:31,510 --> 00:40:34,380
of remorse for what he did. He just threw a massive fit.

635
00:40:35,020 --> 00:40:37,420
There's a limit to how shameless a person can be.

636
00:40:40,420 --> 00:40:42,790
Detective. I'm sorry to ask,

637
00:40:43,220 --> 00:40:44,790
but could I ask you for a favour?

638
00:40:58,870 --> 00:41:02,980
Ma'am, I'm going to need you to take off your sunglasses.

639
00:41:03,240 --> 00:41:04,240
Why?

640
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:08,050
Well, even if you are the victim...

641
00:41:08,780 --> 00:41:11,020
we need to verify your identity and so on.

642
00:41:19,690 --> 00:41:22,160
- I think she's an actress. - Is that really Yu Ji An?

643
00:41:22,300 --> 00:41:24,230
- Isn't she an actress? - She's had work done.

644
00:41:24,300 --> 00:41:25,530
She doesn't look as good as I thought.

645
00:41:25,670 --> 00:41:28,040
How much work has she done on her face? Her eyes, for sure.

646
00:41:28,100 --> 00:41:29,270
She's pretty in person.

647
00:41:31,940 --> 00:41:33,740
So this is what you look like in real life.

648
00:41:35,010 --> 00:41:37,140
So, how did you get scammed like this?

649
00:41:42,180 --> 00:41:44,690
So you're saying you just took the broker's word for it...

650
00:41:44,750 --> 00:41:46,920
and transferred that huge amount of money just like that?

651
00:41:47,420 --> 00:41:48,790
Without even checking the title deed?

652
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:50,160
Title...

653
00:41:51,130 --> 00:41:52,130
and deed?

654
00:41:53,730 --> 00:41:55,700
- What's that? - What?

655
00:41:55,760 --> 00:41:57,560
You just pay the money,

656
00:41:58,300 --> 00:42:00,600
buy the house, and move in.

657
00:42:01,740 --> 00:42:03,040
Isn't that how it works?

658
00:42:04,410 --> 00:42:05,910
I'm buying my own house with my own money.

659
00:42:05,970 --> 00:42:07,370
Why does it have to be so complicated?

660
00:42:08,580 --> 00:42:12,210
I know celebrities can be out of touch, but come on.

661
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:14,450
Good grief.

662
00:42:15,020 --> 00:42:16,680
I'm sorry to call you out of the blue like this...

663
00:42:16,750 --> 00:42:19,720
- especially to ask for a favour. - It's fine. Don't mention it.

664
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:22,820
I'm just returning a favour, so don't feel bad about asking.

665
00:42:23,520 --> 00:42:24,560
Thank you.

666
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:27,830
Okay, I'll look into it and get back to you. You can go now.

667
00:42:28,030 --> 00:42:29,030
Okay.

668
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:31,130
- Take care. - Okay.

669
00:42:31,200 --> 00:42:32,200
Thank you.

670
00:42:34,400 --> 00:42:36,470
Hey, I saw Yu Ji An at the police station.

671
00:42:37,270 --> 00:42:39,570
But it didn't look like she was in trouble, more like she got scammed.

672
00:42:40,070 --> 00:42:42,940
Anyway, she was unreal. A total goddess.

673
00:42:45,750 --> 00:42:46,750
Scammed?

674
00:42:51,790 --> 00:42:53,320
What does that have to do with me?

675
00:42:59,390 --> 00:43:02,229
He could've left after he got a hold of me...

676
00:43:02,230 --> 00:43:03,600
but I guess he was worried about you.

677
00:43:03,930 --> 00:43:05,600
He stayed right by your side.

678
00:43:06,970 --> 00:43:09,270
Anyway, while the landlord was abroad,

679
00:43:09,340 --> 00:43:11,940
the broker intentionally set up a scam and fled.

680
00:43:12,010 --> 00:43:13,810
Catching him is not going to be easy.

681
00:43:14,170 --> 00:43:15,280
Then what about my money?

682
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:18,110
It's best to assume you won't get it back.

683
00:43:18,650 --> 00:43:19,710
What?

684
00:43:22,350 --> 00:43:23,420
Please wait here for a moment.

685
00:43:24,890 --> 00:43:25,890
Yes.

686
00:43:26,990 --> 00:43:28,020
What is it?

687
00:43:50,380 --> 00:43:51,680
Let me see your phone.

688
00:43:52,480 --> 00:43:53,650
Why my phone?

689
00:43:55,020 --> 00:43:56,450
You just took my picture, didn't you?

690
00:43:58,850 --> 00:44:01,290
No, I didn't. Do you have any proof?

691
00:44:01,560 --> 00:44:02,890
Think being a celebrity means you can do anything?

692
00:44:02,960 --> 00:44:04,020
Why are you accusing an innocent person?

693
00:44:04,460 --> 00:44:06,660
I've been in front of the camera for 20 years.

694
00:44:07,260 --> 00:44:08,530
I may not know about title deeds...

695
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:10,300
but just by the camera's position and angle...

696
00:44:10,360 --> 00:44:12,430
I can tell exactly what it's filming.

697
00:44:13,130 --> 00:44:16,540
- Hand it over. Now. - I didn't. What's your problem?

698
00:44:18,710 --> 00:44:19,840
Unbelievable.

699
00:44:20,110 --> 00:44:22,280
No wonder they say you're so entitled.

700
00:44:22,740 --> 00:44:23,740
Seeing how you're acting,

701
00:44:23,741 --> 00:44:27,350
that verbal abuse video must've been real. Right?

702
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:31,250
With a temper like that, it must be true.

703
00:44:31,750 --> 00:44:33,520
Who does she think she is, power-tripping like that?

704
00:44:33,590 --> 00:44:36,120
What's the use of a pretty face when her personality is so ugly?

705
00:44:36,190 --> 00:44:38,660
- A pretty face isn't everything. - She's waiting to crash and burn.

706
00:44:38,730 --> 00:44:41,630
- Why is she on such a power trip? - She acts like she's on a set.

707
00:44:41,730 --> 00:44:43,260
Hey, Yu Ji An. What are you doing?

708
00:44:43,330 --> 00:44:45,000
You should be writing your statement.

709
00:44:45,070 --> 00:44:46,100
Sit down. Now.

710
00:44:46,870 --> 00:44:47,970
Come here. Hurry.

711
00:45:06,420 --> 00:45:08,260
Saw Yu Ji An at the police station.

712
00:45:08,920 --> 00:45:10,120
So ugly in real life.

713
00:45:11,430 --> 00:45:12,660
I'm prettier.

714
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:16,600
What is it?

715
00:45:17,100 --> 00:45:19,099
Taking and posting photos without a person's consent...

716
00:45:19,100 --> 00:45:20,569
is an infringement of their publicity rights...

717
00:45:20,570 --> 00:45:22,100
which is grounds for a civil lawsuit for damages.

718
00:45:24,440 --> 00:45:25,840
Especially for a top star like Yu Ji An,

719
00:45:25,910 --> 00:45:27,340
the amount of damages would be enormous.

720
00:45:28,840 --> 00:45:29,910
Do you think you can handle that?

721
00:45:30,340 --> 00:45:32,580
- Who are you? - This isn't just stating facts.

722
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:34,980
If you add defamation for spreading falsehoods to the mix...

723
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:37,720
your life is going to get a whole lot harder.

724
00:45:37,880 --> 00:45:40,690
- What part of it is false? - Isn't it obvious?

725
00:45:41,860 --> 00:45:42,860
(So Ugly in real life. I'm prettier.)

726
00:45:44,360 --> 00:45:45,490
"So ugly in real life."

727
00:45:46,660 --> 00:45:47,830
And especially this part.

728
00:45:48,930 --> 00:45:50,030
"I'm prettier."

729
00:45:50,300 --> 00:45:51,300
Darn it.

730
00:45:54,130 --> 00:45:56,940
What's your deal, mister? Are you her lawyer or something?

731
00:45:58,370 --> 00:45:59,370
Mister?

732
00:46:00,870 --> 00:46:01,880
No.

733
00:46:03,840 --> 00:46:05,010
I'm a counsellor.

734
00:46:07,280 --> 00:46:08,350
So...

735
00:46:09,580 --> 00:46:10,720
Are you going to delete it?

736
00:46:12,150 --> 00:46:13,290
Or get sued?

737
00:46:34,210 --> 00:46:35,340
I wonder if she's okay.

738
00:46:35,910 --> 00:46:37,410
Getting scammed like that...

739
00:46:38,710 --> 00:46:39,910
Don't worry about me.

740
00:46:41,480 --> 00:46:42,620
I'm fine.

741
00:46:43,450 --> 00:46:46,250
Wait, what? I'm sure I only thought to myself.

742
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:57,400
Getting scammed is frustrating,

743
00:46:58,400 --> 00:46:59,870
but they'll catch the person who did it...

744
00:47:01,470 --> 00:47:02,940
and I can always make more money.

745
00:47:05,140 --> 00:47:06,470
I'm Yu Ji An, after all.

746
00:47:11,510 --> 00:47:12,810
Right, well...

747
00:47:14,080 --> 00:47:15,450
Thanks for your help today.

748
00:47:16,780 --> 00:47:17,780
I'll get going, then.

749
00:47:25,890 --> 00:47:26,890
Are you okay?

750
00:47:33,730 --> 00:47:34,970
I'm fine.

751
00:47:36,770 --> 00:47:38,140
I said I'm fine.

752
00:47:39,810 --> 00:47:42,280
Why do you keep asking if I'm okay?

753
00:47:43,540 --> 00:47:44,640
When you keep...

754
00:47:45,910 --> 00:47:48,220
asking me if I'm okay,

755
00:47:51,120 --> 00:47:52,120
it makes me feel like...

756
00:47:54,350 --> 00:47:57,020
I'm actually not okay.

